# Microservice java package and class naming conventions

## Codeing instructions
Follow the strategy in table to generate code using the java package and class naming conventions.

| Purpose                    | Java Package Conventions       | Java type naming |
|----------------------------|--------------------------------|-----------------------|
| controller impl class      | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.controllers    | suffix: Controller |
| controller interfaces      | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.api            | suffix: Api |
| controller request DTO     | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.controller.dto | suffix: Request |
| controller response DTO    | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.controller.dto | suffix: Response |
| spring service impl class  | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.services       | suffix: Service |
| spring service interface   | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.services.api   | suffix: Service |
| main app class             | com.rcl.{{projectPackage}}.App            | classname: App       |
| exception definitions      | todo | todo |
| error code definitions     | todo | todo |
| Global exception handler   | TODO | TODO   |
